items.name: White Eyes v2
items.description:
I couldn't prompt white eyes — you know, like without any iris or pupil? No matter how hard I tried, I couldn't do it. I just wanted to make a bunch of spooky photos! So I made this LoRA.

My friend said I should add a donation link, so here. Go nuts. (Or if you're poor, like me, maybe leave the LoRA a glowing review instead. You can't eat praise, but man it feels good.)

This is a better version of my first LoRA, after I spent a month trying to understand stuff like learning rates and schedulers and weight decay.

Have fun, and let me know what you think!

Some tips:

  • Depending on the model you're using, adding the words "white eyes" into the prompt (in addition to using the trigger word) can be helpful.

  • Same goes for adjusting the LoRA strength. For example, in A-ZovyaPhotoreal try turning it up a little for younger people, and up more for older people.

  • I'll probably think of more.

items.name: Meryl NotExist
items.description:
Who is she? The stylish politician? The smart lawyer? The mum whose kids has left home who still turns a few head? She's no-one who exists, but is here as an embedding.

I recommend you use ADetailer to show it at its best.

I wanted to do an older, but still glamourous character. It didn't turn out quite as old as I wanted, but AgeSlider is really good at adding those final few wrinkles.

This uses the same method I describe here, but with my more recent lessons in doing embeddings. Basically I found a face I liked in Stable Diffusion then used Faceapp to map it onto a set of faces, and then used that to train an embedding.

This one came from a character in my Big City Girls story on Deviant art (muscle growth, boob growth - though the embedding is her as a normal woman) and I sensed I would want to write her again, so tried the method and it worked pretty well.

Here's the story episode where I debut the embedding.

modelVersions.name: v2.5
modelVersions.description:
After getting really frustrated trying to mix and improve 2.0 various days, I decided to base this version on 1.5 again, using the same mixes of 2.0 in different percentages. Included models I used before or previous versions of this model with some additions.

I find it at least easier to use than 2.0 and the results are clean, and cleaner faces on group photos. I recommend to use Euler A or DDIM for easier results, but 2M++ SDE Karras and 3M++ SDE karras are good too.

I used the Kf8Anime and FtMse840000vae for the preview photos, with Adetailer and Tiled Vae. If there is a picture with more than 10 Cfg scale, I probably used the Dynamic Thresholding Extension with that one, I put a link in the description of the model if you are interested.

Also I want to merge some loras in the next version of the model, but It's really confusing, If someone knows how to use the Super Merger extension and can help me, I will be eternally grateful. It's hard to find any info online and I find the tutorial of the official page kinda cryptic.

Welp, it seems that every version I get out it's more tricky to use than the one before, this one seems to know a lot of concepts tho, and that's amazing... If you can pull it off. I don't like that too much because my goal was to make an easy to use model. I will try to make it easier somehow in the next versions.

One tip I discovered, if you get random penis where they shouldn't be, in hands or mouths, or even in other penises while generating a sex scene, just get rid of the "penis tag". Sometimes some concepts have already a penis on it by default and it weirdly generates some more with that tag on it.

If you want an easier version to use, use one of the previous versions, but with a bit of experimentation and effort this one can do a lot of sex related stuff and other concepts.

I reccomend FtMse840000 vae for this one maybe klfl8Anime works fine too. Also I started to use DPM++ 3M SDE Karras and it seems to work quite well. At least with my prompts + Adetailer + Tiled Vae

items.name: Art Styles Expansion for StyleSelectorXL
items.description:
This is an expansion for the StyleSelectorXL extension. To make this work you'll need StyleSelectorXL: https://github.com/ahgsql/StyleSelectorXL.git

Version 2 of this expansion adds many visual styles and art styles to the SDXL Style Selector menu. These are compiled from the original Style Selector XL style list, the ComfyUI SDXL Prompt Styler style list, and the Fooocus Styles menu style list - plus I've added my own 70+ styles.

The styles list has been pruned to exclude exact duplicate prompts, and I've also put the styles in alphabetical order for ease of use. This brings the styles list to 190 different art styles and visual styles.

Please Note that while the extension says "XL" it does work quite well with both SDXL 1.0 models AND SD 1.5 models.

While it does seem to do best with photo/realistic based models, it can create gorgeous works with more stylized models as well. So feel free to use it with a variety of your favorite checkpoints/models.

It took some research on different art styles to know how to prompt for the different styles and I learned a lot. They're not 100% perfect, as many styles are new to me and I had to make educated guesses based on the style's descriptions on how to build the prompt scripts for them. So they might not be 100% true to the different styles, but they do add a nice amount of artistic variety!

This expansion took quite a few hours to compile and create, so if you have a minute please leaving a rating for this. I'd very much appreciate it! :)

If you enjoy this or get some creative fun out of it please consider donating: https://ko-fi.com/3diva

~ Diva

items.name: Desi Skin Tone Slider +/- (LECO LoRA, SD 1.5, Experimental)
items.description:
Want to know how to create these? Read my tutorial here: https://civitai.com/articles/1891/guide-to-training-sliders-adjusters

Follow up to my Desiness LECO LoRA.

This particular LoRA allows you to shift base Indian/ South Asian skintones from Dark (Weight: -1) to Light Skinned (Weight: +1), without making the tones so light that the person looks white.

In order to get the Indian look, use the phrase 'Indian Woman' in the prompt, or like I have, use any of my Desi textual inversions (embeddings). In this case I have used 'desidressed'.

On a more philosophical note, it is interesting to see how the change in skin tone also changes the background and the clothing. This is something I'll try to control for in my next go around, but curious nonetheless.

Comments/ suggestions are welcome!

items.name: US Navy Standard Missile
items.description:
The Standard Missile 2 (SM-2) is the U.S Navy's primary surface-to-air air defense weapon. It is an integral part of the AEGIS Weapon System (AWS) aboard Ticonderoga-class cruisers and Arleigh Burke-class destroyers; and is launched from the Mark 41 vertical launcher system (VLS). Its primary missions are fleet area air defense and ship self-defense, but it also has demonstrated an extended area air defense projection capability. The SM-2 uses tail controls and a solid fuel rocket motor for propulsion and maneuverability. All variants are guided by inertial navigation and mid-course commands from AWS using semi-active radar or an infrared (IR) sensor for terminal homing.

Version 2-XL:

This LoRA was trained using the SDXL base model. I noticed that choosing the expontential/polyexponential noise schedule can produce better images than Karras.

Trigger token: sdMS2 / sdMS2 missile

Version 1:

This LoRA (LoCon) was trained with SD1.5 as the source model. Euler, Euler a, and DPM++ 2M SDE generally work well. Version 1.1 is more of an alternative, I'd say the images are generally better but it is possible that the old version performs better in some cases.

Trigger tokens: aegism2 / aegism2 missile


Trained using images published by the US Missile Defense Agency:

MDA - Media Library
